eir turn in the lead, they're not keen.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524843fee4b09c02a13addf2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T16:15:22.604+01:00\">4.15pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Crash! Rigoberto Uran goes arse very much over tit into a grass verge coming round a left-hander, and that's his race over.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T16:15:57.148+01:00\">at 4.15pm BST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-5248438ee4b008dd84fc9737\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T16:13:19.471+01:00\">4.13pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Nibali takes the lead, but Rodriguez sticks with him. Those two have swiftly opened a bit of a gap, three more five seconds behind, and then the rest after a 10sec gap.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524842f7e4b0f2e0c754380f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T16:10:49.017+01:00\">4.10pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>I keep trying to say who's leading, but it keeps changing. At this very moment, it's Joaquin Rodriguez. Scarponi and Nibali are in the front few. I feel for these cyclists: this is gruelling enough to liveblog (with a lunch break).</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52484204e4b0c07967813b4d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T16:07:23.379+01:00\">4.07pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>No big breaks as yet. Jakob Fluglsang leads.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/cyclingweekly/statuses/384332884628090880\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>42 riders in front group inc Gilbert/Degenkolb/Clarke/Nibali/Sagan/Cancellara/