3f96e4b09c02a13addee\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:56:23.404+01:00\">3.56pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Romain Bardet has gone out in front, and Michele Scarponi keeps him company. They have an extremely slender lead, perhaps 10m of it.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483ef7e4b09c02a13added\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:53:44.349+01:00\">3.53pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The leaders head, for the penultimate time, up Via Salviati. Jonathan Castroviejo leads them up. No one is making a tilt at glory, yet.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483e2de4b008dd84fc9730\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:50:52.515+01:00\">3.50pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>So the current situation in brief: 36 riders remain in contention. One of them will win.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384328763619540995\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>36 riders left in the peloton, Belgium in the lead. Last lap approaching. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Toscana2013_eng (@Toscana2013_eng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384328763619540995\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483d3fe4b008dd84fc972f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:48:29.390+01:00\">3.48pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>All the key favourites are, then, still up there with 27km to go. Pauwels now in the lead, followed by Maxim Iglinskiy of Kazakhstan, with Nibali 11th. Belgium and Colombia are the two strongest teams, but it's getting close to the point where the individuals take over.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384328164316430336\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Contador dropped <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Toscana2013_eng (@Toscana2013_eng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384328164316430336\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483ceae4b008dd84fc972e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:44:59.187+01:00\">3.44pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The leaders have been caught, and there's now a Columbian in the lead. Nibali is perhaps 15th.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483c75e4b0f2e0c7543807\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:44:01.494+01:00\">3.44pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Nibali is back in the pack, an astonishing effort in itself, and they're moving fast. He was helped by some convenient assistance from the team car, which he clung on to for a while while his, um, mechanical problems were, er, fixed. The leaders' lead is diminishing rapidly. 12 seconds now.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483b73e4b09c02a13addeb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:40:09.575+01:00\">3.40pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Thirty kilometres to go, Visconti now 45 seconds ahead of the peloton, and Nibali another 16 seconds back, desperately trying to catch up.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483b07e4b008dd84fc972d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:38:22.361+01:00\">3.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>When the dust settles, there are going to be a lot of disappointed athletes with interesting stories. Here, in brief, is that of Dan Martin, who says it's the &quot;worst conditions I've ever seen&quot;</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/DanMartin86/statuses/384325237414051840\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Quick crash that. Couldn't avoid the guy on the floor in front of me. Slid forever. Bad luck but I'm ok unlike a lot of others.</p>— Dan Martin (@DanMartin86) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/DanMartin86/statuses/384325237414051840\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/DanMartin86/statuses/384325534840520704\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Took me a while to find my bike though. Wonder how many crashes there were? Worst conditions I've ever seen. Florence airport is closed!</p>— Dan Martin (@DanMartin86) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/DanMartin86/statuses/384325534840520704\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483a7fe4b008dd84fc972c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:34:40.334+01:00\">3.34pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The leaders cross the finish line, two laps to go, which should take in the region of 45 minutes, in improving conditions. The Belgians remain at the front of the peloton.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524839d7e4b0c07967813b48\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:32:28.863+01:00\">3.32pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>With no team radio, Visconti might not know – might not know for some time – that he is now his country's only hope of victory.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248399fe4b09c02a13addea\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:31:30.387+01:00\">3.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Nibali falls!</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The front two have a 1min 15sec lead on the peloton. A little further back, Vincenzo Nibali and Luca Paolini have fallen! Nibali is back on his bike, but in deep trouble.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483915e4b008dd84fc972b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:28:39.020+01:00\">3.28pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Huzarski is now in second place, Visconti taking over at the front. Two laps and a little bit to go.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248384fe4b09c02a13adde9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:26:08.784+01:00\">3.26pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Huzarski sets off up the short and very far from sweet Via Salviati. Visconti is perhaps 100m behind him, but it's a very steep 100m.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Procycling_Week/statuses/384322356572741633\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>40km lefts now. Visconti is chasing Huzarski very hard. Visconti won two stages of the Giro with solo efforts <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Pro Cycling Week (@Procycling_Week) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Procycling_Week/statuses/384322356572741633\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524837e6e4b09c02a13adde8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:23:36.347+01:00\">3.23pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>&quot;Though I wouldn't recommend cycling 280kms in it, the rain in the hills above Florence is very pleasant indeed - big fat drops that are splashy and warm, rather than hard and cold,&quot; writes Gary Naylor. &quot;And, once you get inside, it doesn't half make those big red wines taste good.&quot; Those big red wines taste pretty fine without having to get rained on at all, in my experience.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483729e4b09c02a13adde7\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:21:14.051+01:00\">3.21pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Sunshine! There is sun! In Italy! And it's shining on Visconti, who is about 1min 10sec ahead of the peloton, and 18sec behind Huzarski.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483648e4b0f2e0c7543800\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:17:19.303+01:00\">3.17pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Movement! Giovanni Visconti overtakes Barta, with Huzarski now on alone in front. It seems quite popular with the fans.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483620e4b0c07967813b46\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:16:01.410+01:00\">3.16pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>They've been going for six hours and 15 minutes. Still one more to go. Sheesh.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483586e4b09c02a13adde6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:14:25.173+01:00\">3.14pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Geraint Thomas speaks: He says Froome didn't have the best day, and &quot;it's not the weather for Brad&quot;. &quot;The rest of us didn't really have the legs to do anthing in the final,&quot; he says. &quot;It was just carnage out there. As soon as you drift to the second half of the peloton there's just crashes everywhere. I think I saw at least five or six big crashes. Once you're in that back half you're destined to get dropped really. We all committed to try and get Froomey there, but it didn't happen. First time up the climb we were all sort of there, and when the Italians went we were in a good position there, but it was just hard. Not a lot we could have done, when you don't have the legs.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524834f3e4b008dd84fc9725\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:11:33.686+01:00\">3.11pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Barta and Huzarski deserve some kind of medal after this, whatever happens to them. Remarkable, to lead for so long.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524833dde4b0f2e0c75437fb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:07:33.902+01:00\">3.07pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The peloton crosses the finish line, about a minute and a half behind Visconti/Gaultier. Three laps, perhaps an hour and 15 minutes, to go and if these three pairs can become a front four or even a leading six, things might get interesting.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483315e4b0c07967813b45\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:04:29.481+01:00\">3.04pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Chris Froome tells the BBC: &quot;It's a big disappointment especially having trained so hard. I think with these conditions here today it just weasn't to be. The first three laps we did on the circuit here, even before that, there were crashes everywhere. It's just the weather, it hasn't let up all day. At some points we were a foot deep in water. After three laps the split started happening. I looked around and saw I didn't have any teammates with me and thought, 'This is not going to happen for me today.' The conditions are the same for everyone so we've got no excuse, we just weren't there today.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248329ee4b0c07967813b44\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T15:02:15.178+01:00\">3.02pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>I tell a lie: Austria's Georg Preidler and Wilco Kelderman are between the front two and the Visconti/Gaultier double chase, with the three pairs split by about 45sec.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524831fce4b0c07967813b43\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:59:04.214+01:00\">2.59pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Television pictures reinforce the sheer dampness of the race, as Visconti and Gaultier come within a couple of hundred metres of the leading pair.</p> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-1fb43cb5-53d8-41dd-9798-bf52516ffc9a\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/9/29/1380463099494/ad9279e1-227a-4174-b207-c75240c93015-460x276.png\" alt=\"Italy's Giovanni Visconti and Cyril Gaultier of France during the men's elite race, at the road cycling world championships\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Italy's Giovanni Visconti and Cyril Gaultier of France during the men's elite race, at the road cycling world championships Photograph: /BBC</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248312ae4b008dd84fc971e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:55:26.202+01:00\">2.55pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Another attack, this one led by Italy's Giovanni Visconti, shadowed only by Cyril Gautier of France.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:55:40.455+01:00\">at 2.55pm BST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-524830d5e4b0f2e0c75437fa\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:53:42.278+01:00\">2.53pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The thunder rumbles as the front two head down the hill towards Florance for the last-but-oneth time.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52483077e4b0f2e0c75437f9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:52:21.399+01:00\">2.52pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The push from Stetina has really eaten into the lead enjoyed by the front two, which has halved to 1m 15sec in no time at all.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482f66e4b09c02a13adddf\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:48:46.018+01:00\">2.48pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The front of the peloton has been split by a little attack, which has left all but one of the Italians behind. Peter Stetina leads it, followed by Thomas Voeckler, and perhaps a dozen others.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482e6be4b0c07967813b3e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:44:47.931+01:00\">2.44pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Belgium team is going strong, but for the crashed and retired Bjorn Leukemans. The rest of them have taken over from the Italians at the front, with the reigning champions Philippe Gilbert among them. Now appearing to their left, five Frenchmen.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482ce5e4b008dd84fc9716\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:38:23.509+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>It's still raining on the front two, who are still over two minutes ahead. Barta and Huzarski are teammates with NetApp-Endura, and are clearly cooperating nicely here.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482b02e4b09c02a13addde\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:30:45.283+01:00\">2.30pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>&quot;This is crazy, elemental sport,&quot; offers Gary Naylor. &quot;Surely, in any other race playing out in these conditions, the competitors would be taking it easy, but the crashes and retirements show that they're not. Perhaps only National Hunt racing – with which cycling shares a few problems – makes such demands on its participants with so little regard for their 'comfort. Every man who finishes today is a winner – as is anyone who makes it to the Champs Elysees or Roubaix.&quot;</p> <p>I've got a lot of sympathy with those who don't finish, and not just because some of them will have crashed. In a one-off race like this, in grim conditions, what would make you keep going once you knew you couldn't podium?</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482a58e4b0c07967813b38\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:27:05.428+01:00\">2.27pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>So, Cancellara, Gilbert or Nibali? The three of them make up about 4.3% of the remaining competitors – who of the other 95.7% could stop them?</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384307556241260544\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Today's race is pretty extreme. About 70 riders left. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Toscana2013_eng (@Toscana2013_eng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384307556241260544\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482921e4b0f2e0c75437f1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:21:34.413+01:00\">2.21pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Hello again. Thomas's exit has been confirmed, so at the precise moment when coverage shifts to BBC2 to allow the nation to follow Froome's final push for glory, we learn that there are no British or Irish riders remaining in the race.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524828a5e4b09c02a13adddc\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:19:38.328+01:00\">2.19pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Geraint Thomas appears to have called it a day too - it's been reported that he's back at the team bus, completing a miserable day for Britain's riders. And on that note, I'll hand you back to Simon.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52482641e4b09c02a13addda\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:13:25.386+01:00\">2.13pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Meanwhile the Italians and Belgians are duking it out at the front of the peleton, with five laps to go, with Vanotti at its head. All four Irish riders are out of the race too.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524823f7e4b008dd84fc9714\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T14:04:35.332+01:00\">2.04pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Froome's withdrawal has been confirmed, leaving Geraint Thomas as the sole British rider in the race.</p> <p>Huzarski and Barta are now around two minutes ahead of the peleton and half a minute ahead of Brandle, working well together at 37km per hour on a challenging hilly stretch. About 85km to go.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248217de4b008dd84fc9711\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:54:29.350+01:00\">1.54pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Chris Froome is out of this</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Godoy and Brandle are now struggling to stay with the pace of the leaders too as we enter the last 100km, as Barta and Huzarski stretch their lead, and it's all over for Froome.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/willfoth/statuses/384299037949558784\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>End of the road for Froome. Not a great day for GB, not a great championship.</p>— William Fotheringham (@willfoth) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/willfoth/statuses/384299037949558784\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524820c5e4b09c02a13addd4\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:45:32.468+01:00\">1.45pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>I'm going to grab some lunch – nobody runs around Guardian towers waving bags of munchables for busy MBMers, sadly. Tom Davies will keep you up to date until I return.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248206fe4b09c02a13addd3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:44:35.684+01:00\">1.44pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Rafaa Chtioui has been sneezed out by the leading five, and will be the first to be caught by the peloton.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248203de4b0c07967813b31\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:43:13.711+01:00\">1.43pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Froome is quite close to being out of contention now, it seems. His second group, which is actually the third group, is being slowly left behind.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384296634122637312\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Peloton at 1'35 from leading group. 55' between the first and the second chasing group <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Toscana2013_eng (@Toscana2013_eng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384296634122637312\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481fbee4b0c07967813b30\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:41:05.683+01:00\">1.41pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>This from Ireland's Matt Brammeier:</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Mattbrammeier85/statuses/384296385287581696\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Holy hell. That was a circus. We did what we could but there's only so many bodies you can dodge! Real shame for <a href=\"https://twitter.com/DanMartin86\">@DanMartin86</a></p>— Matt Brammeier (@Mattbrammeier85) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Mattbrammeier85/statuses/384296385287581696\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Mattbrammeier85/statuses/384296472168386560\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Whoever wins this race is one hell of a bike rider</p>— Matt Brammeier (@Mattbrammeier85) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Mattbrammeier85/statuses/384296472168386560\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481f1ee4b0f2e0c75437e9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:39:03.159+01:00\">1.39pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The leaders have less than 100km to go now, which is a major psychological breakthrough both for them and, I'll admit it, for me. A fascinating few hours await.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481e39e4b09c02a13addd1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:35:23.508+01:00\">1.35pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>For all the panic and the rainfall, the top four pre-race favourites – Cancellara, Sagan, Gilbert and Nibali – would still be the favourites now. Froome, who was sixth favourite when the race started, would no longer rank so high. He's about 40sec behind the Italians at the front of the peloton now.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481ddae4b09c02a13addd0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:32:58.562+01:00\">1.32pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The front five, having enjoyed leadership for several aeons, now have a 1.30min gap, and will be eaten up within the next lap.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SkyOrla/statuses/384292128635244544\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Ian Stannard just arrived back at team bus looking spent. &quot;They're coming down like skittles out there.&quot;</p>— Orla Chennaoui (@SkyOrla) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SkyOrla/statuses/384292128635244544\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481d94e4b0c07967813b2d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:31:38.914+01:00\">1.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>There will be no American victor today, things having started to go wrong for them pretty early.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/taylorphinney/statuses/384292346168631296\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Well, shit. Was taking care of Tejay today but unfortunately he crashed on the 1st lap. I waited for him, chased, but we never made it back.</p>— Taylor Phinney (@taylorphinney) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/taylorphinney/statuses/384292346168631296\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481bb7e4b008dd84fc970b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:23:42.321+01:00\">1.23pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Thunderbolts and lightning in Tuscany, but it's the following that will be very very frightening to British readers:</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384292052810215424\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Froome in drop group <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Toscana2013_eng (@Toscana2013_eng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Toscana2013_eng/statuses/384292052810215424\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481b04e4b0f2e0c75437e3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:21:36.733+01:00\">1.21pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The leading five are now a little over two minutes ahead of the peloton, down from a peak of eight and a half or so.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524819f7e4b008dd84fc9709\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:16:15.710+01:00\">1.16pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>&quot;This day is so reminiscent of Oslo in 1993,&quot; writes Gary Naylor. &quot;That edition was won by a brilliant young rider, whose tactical acumen and superb bike handling marked him out for future greatness. Whatever happened to Lance Armstrong?&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524819a2e4b008dd84fc9708\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:15:14.415+01:00\">1.15pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>There are about 20 riders in the peloton, also including Peter Sagan – harder to track since he swapped his bike for one with no timing gizmo – and then Froome is in a second group about 10 seconds further back.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Procycling_Week/statuses/384289361052721152\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Looks to be about 20 riders in this front group. Cancellara, Pozzato, Gilbert &amp; van Avermaet in there <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Pro Cycling Week (@Procycling_Week) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Procycling_Week/statuses/384289361052721152\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481888e4b09c02a13addcb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:10:54.705+01:00\">1.10pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Froome has in fact found himself in the wrong bit of a split peloton, and has launched a solo bid to catch the leading pack. The Italians still look well positioned. These are critical moments for Froome's chances.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481823e4b008dd84fc9706\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:08:20.354+01:00\">1.08pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-a8cc2bdb-1942-4d7d-89dc-dbff663fe942\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/9/29/1380456479218/fa907932-8f58-4fd0-b206-d0eaf882a5b4-460x276.jpeg\" alt=\"A cyclist crashed during the Elite Men's road race of the UCI Road Cycling World Championships 2013 in Florence.\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>A cyclist crashed during the Elite Men's road race of the UCI Road Cycling World Championships 2013 in Florence. Photograph: Maurizio Degl'Innocenti/EPA</figcaption> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/jeremyroy/statuses/384288419716681728\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Carnage !! <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a></p>— Jeremy Roy (@jeremyroy) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jeremyroy/statuses/384288419716681728\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:12:12.350+01:00\">at 1.12pm BST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-524817aee4b09c02a13addca\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:06:42.950+01:00\">1.06pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Froome remains in the peloton, though not very close to the front of it, and without an enormous amount of British support.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248170fe4b09c02a13addc9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T13:04:37.742+01:00\">1.04pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Whoever wins this will deserve some serious admiration, though the conditions mean he may be the luckiest, rather than the best.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/sticky_bottle/statuses/384287227347341312\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Just when you thought the rain couldn't get heavier in Florence, it does. Thunder now too and getting really cold now. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?