s\"> <p>As the peloton headed up Via Salvati on their first lap, it was a massive huddle of bike and muscle. It's massively smaller now than it was then, stretched out by the Italians and the conditions.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524812b9e4b0f2e0c75437e0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:45:24.634+01:00\">12.45pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Evans, Acevedo and Dan Martin were all among the 15 riders caught in that crash. The rain is getting heavier, if anything.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248120ae4b008dd84fc9703\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:43:01.231+01:00\">12.43pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>A crash! This looks grim – bodies littering the side of the street, unmoving. In these conditions, it's not hard to imagine more of these. I'm not sure who was involved, though Cadel Evans has been mentioned. More to come.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52481176e4b0f2e0c75437df\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:40:56.998+01:00\">12.40pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>A picture! As I say, there haven't been many, but here's one. The weather looks a lot worse on TV than it does here.</p> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-d5e11b96-1987-4c44-ac0a-c20e457db44d\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/9/29/1380454774007/a66ab558-f0ab-4f10-8e13-043c71526fd5-460x276.jpeg\" alt=\"Cyclists ride past Florence's Santa Maria del Fiore Basilica during the men's elite race at the road cycling world championships in Tuscany.\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Cyclists ride past Florence's Santa Maria del Fiore Basilica during the men's elite race at the road cycling world championships in Tuscany. Photograph: Fabrizio Giovannozzi/AP</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248103fe4b0f2e0c75437de\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:35:59.005+01:00\">12.35pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Wiggins is out!</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Sir Bradley of Wiggins and Lord Mark Cavendish, the latter after leading the peloton for a good while, the former after, well, presumably after remembering that he doesn't much like going down wet Italian hills, have quit, and there are now six Britons left on the road.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480fb8e4b0f2e0c75437dd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:33:00.572+01:00\">12.33pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Brits have slipped a way back, with Froome now 70th, though only moments behind the leaders of the peloton, who are all Italian.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480ef8e4b09c02a13addc5\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:29:26.173+01:00\">12.29pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Eyewitnesses suggest Wiggins is still on his bike, but clearly he has slipped back into irrelevance.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480de8e4b0c07967813b2a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:26:35.256+01:00\">12.26pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Sagan has been forced into a bike swap, but it didn't massively inconvenience him. The Italians are pushing hard at the front of the peloton, with the gap on the leaders now below six minutes.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480cb2e4b0c07967813b29\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:19:35.649+01:00\">12.19pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Chris Horner and Daryl Impey have both come off their bikes, I'm hearing.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480c18e4b0c07967813b28\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:17:19.884+01:00\">12.17pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>I'm not sure what's going on with Wiggins at the moment, or even if he's still involved. Twitter seems as good a source as any…</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/storejep/statuses/384274296245190656\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Bradley Wiggins abandons right now, says Danish Coach Bonde from the car <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#toscana2013</a></p>— Jeppe Helbo (@storejep) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/storejep/statuses/384274296245190656\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480b47e4b008dd84fc96ff\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:13:38.303+01:00\">12.13pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Poland's Bartosz Huzarski crosses the finish line in first place. Sadly for him, there are still nine laps to go.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480a65e4b008dd84fc96fe\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:09:49.581+01:00\">12.09pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The latest from our man in Tuscany, William Fotheringham:</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/willfoth/statuses/384271262333161472\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Smashing down in Forence. Nibali said yesterday that rain dances don't always work, clearly this one did</p>— William Fotheringham (@willfoth) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/willfoth/statuses/384271262333161472\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524809dee4b008dd84fc96fd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:07:51.218+01:00\">12.07pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>&quot;I'm getting constant reports of small crashes all the time,&quot; say the BBC's commentator. We haven't seen any of them, not one. Other than suggesting that &quot;a Polish rider&quot; has been involved, we get no further information.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248090be4b0c07967813b27\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:06:05.643+01:00\">12.06pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Two Italians – waterproof jackets covering their race numbers, unhelpfully – catch up with the British peloton leaders, swiftly followed by several teammates. With all the raindrops and everything, it's pretty hard to identify individuals from distant helicam shots.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480838e4b0f2e0c75437dc\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T12:02:01.010+01:00\">12.02pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The peloton is on the way up to Fiesole, a 4.37km climb that averages 5.2% but peaks at 9%. The other noteworthy climb, 4.5km or so later, is Via Salvati, much smaller – 0.6km – but steeper – averaging 10.2%, peaking at 16%.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5248072ce4b0f2e0c75437db\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:57:04.855+01:00\">11.57am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Rafaa Chtioui, whose surname reads like something you see on Countdown before the clever people make words out of it, is at the very front at the moment. I can make &quot;touch&quot; for five.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524806d7e4b0f2e0c75437da\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:55:19.665+01:00\">11.55am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Alberto Contador has gone down in a mini-crash, also featuring one of the Lithuanian cyclists and a motorbike-mounted cameraman possibly contributing.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480615e4b008dd84fc96fb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:53:44.100+01:00\">11.53am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>It looks like it isn't raining at all on the ascent to Fiesole, to judge by the lack of umbrellas being wielded by spectators watching the front five, who currently enjoy a 7:44min advantage. Florence itself, where the peloton is still rolling, is ludicrously damp. Bradley Wiggins has been spotted, pretty close to the back. The rest of the Brits are nicely poised near the front.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524804a9e4b0f2e0c75437d9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:46:15.106+01:00\">11.46am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Jan Barta of the Czech Republic is in the lead, as the peloton zips past the duomo. Malaysia's Sea Keong Leoh is currently losing. Every time I've been the Florence one part of the cathedral or another has been covered with scaffolding. Not today.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524803cee4b008dd84fc96fa\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:41:50.431+01:00\">11.41am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>&quot;I wouldn't want to descend in training in this kind of weather, let alone race it,&quot; says Armitstead.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480388e4b008dd84fc96f9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:41:10.900+01:00\">11.41am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The pictures have now frozen entirely, presumably because Florence is suffering an enormous technoflood. &quot;The rain here can best be described as torrential,&quot; says the commentators. In some countries you can watch live coverage on YouTube <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I9_YbtPUgXY\">here</a>.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524802b6e4b0f2e0c75437d8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:38:19.669+01:00\">11.38am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Not many pictures coming through our picture wires, so I've grabbed this from the BBC's TV coverage. It is wet, like I say.</p> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-6467e821-1c08-4e7f-919b-5da314d5be6a\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/9/29/1380451085411/92beed76-e5ff-48f3-ab86-04e632956bc7-460x276.png\" alt=\"Road World Championships 2013: men's road race\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Rain falls on the leaders of the men's road race at the 2013 Road World Championships. Photograph: /BBC</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52480176e4b008dd84fc96f8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:32:42.842+01:00\">11.32am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Lizzie Armitstead, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2013/sep/28/marianne-vos-world-cycling-championships\">who came 19th in yesterday's women's race</a>, thinks the descents today will be &quot;quite dangerous&quot;, and it's not hard to believe her as the support cars switch their windscreen wipers to maximum.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-524800c9e4b0f2e0c75437d7\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:29:26.683+01:00\">11.29am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>At the front of the peloton is the British trio of Mark Cavendish, Luke Rowe and Geraint Thomas. I've not seen much of Froome, as of yet.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247ffb7e4b0c07967813b26\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:25:27.397+01:00\">11.25am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The run from Lucca to Florence measured 106.6km. Each lap of the Firenze-Fiesole circuit measures 16.6km, and like I say there are 10 of them. So they are 39% of the way through the race.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247ff26e4b0f2e0c75437d6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:23:13.528+01:00\">11.23am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The leaders have just passed a pretty roundabout-based floral arrangement resembling the badge of Florence, which suggests they're arriving in the city and preparing to launch themselves on the first of 10 laps of a circuit widely described as &quot;hilly&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247fe4de4b09c02a13addc2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:18:54.421+01:00\">11.18am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Yonder Godoy, the current race leader, is the youngest rider in the race at 20 years, five months and some days. He came 36th in this year's Vuelta Ciclista a Venezuela.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247fd3de4b0c07967813b25\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:15:32.863+01:00\">11.15am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>I did think that someone had invented a way of keeping rainwater off television cameras, but either it hasn't reached Italy yet, or it's so wet there's nothing anyone can do about it, because I've seen dryer glass in aquariums. Every image is obscured by a hundred irritating raindrops. Bah.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247fcabe4b09c02a13addc1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:11:52.334+01:00\">11.11am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bad news for Sir Brad</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The peloton has split, and Wiggins – who called for the team car, for reasons unknown, perhaps 10 minutes back – is in the wrong half. It is <em>really</em> wet out there.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247fc31e4b09c02a13addc0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:09:57.753+01:00\">11.09am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>There's a breakway group, whose lead is currently around the six-minute mark, featuring a small handful of rank outsiders including Venezuela's Yonder Godoy, Poland's Bartosz Huzarski and Tunisia's Rafaa Chtioui.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5247f711e4b09c02a13addbf\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-09-29T11:08:27.241+01:00\">11.08am <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Morning world!</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The race is already under way in Tuscany, in imperfect, damp conditions. Raindrop-splodged helicams are following the leaders, with our own Mark Cavendish currently at the head of the peloton, but there's a long way to go yet. It may be helpful to have a full list of competitors, and that follows after this small selection of pre-race tweets. I should warn you, though: there are 207 of them.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/PhilippeGilbert/statuses/384201701986959360\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Goodmorning to all,rain here but not cold so I don't complain.I expect a great atmosphere and a lot of support from the crowd!<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23belgiumpower&amp;src=hash\">#belgiumpower</a></p>— PHILIPPE GILBERT (@PhilippeGilbert) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/PhilippeGilbert/statuses/384201701986959360\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/f_cancellara/statuses/384201770417008640\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Today it will be a 272km race in pain....!!!!! <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Toscana2013&amp;src=hash\">#Toscana2013</a> switzerland will go for it.! One nation one team</p>— Fabian cancellara (@f_cancellara) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/f_cancellara/statuses/384201770417008640\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/alejanvalverde/statuses/383958526353080320\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>I would like to add the golden one to the collection. I will give it all tomorrow to try and get it. <a href=\"http://t.co/2Vn50J1jVo\">pic.twitter.com/2Vn50J1jVo</a></p>— alejandro valverde (@alejanvalverde) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/alejanvalverde/statuses/383958526353080320\">September 28, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/ThorHushovd/statuses/384206860657917952\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Ready to race <a href=\"http://t.co/HDtfnNFANl\">http://t.co/HDtfnNFANl</a></p>— Thor Hushovd (@ThorHushovd) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ThorHushovd/statuses/384206860657917952\">September 29, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <h2>Those riders in full</h2> <p><strong>BELGIUM</strong><br />1 GILBERT Philippe<br />2 BAKELANTS Jan<br />3 LEUKEMANS Bjorn<br />4 MONFORT Maxime<br />5 PAUWELS Serge<br />6 VAN AVERMAET Greg<br />7 VAN SUMMEREN Johan</p> <p><strong>SPAIN</strong><br />8 CASTROVIEJO NICOLAS Jonathan<br />9 CONTADOR VELASCO Alberto<br />10 HERRADA LOPEZ Jose<br />11 MARTINEZ DE ESTEBAN Egoi<br />12 MORENO FERNANDEZ Daniel<br />13 RODRIGUEZ OLIVER Joaquin<br />14 SANCHEZ GIL Luis Leon<br />15 SANCHEZ GONZALEZ Samuel<br />16 VALVERDE BELMONTE Alejandro</p> <p><strong>ITALY</strong><br />17 NIBALI Vincenzo<br />18 NOCENTINI Rinaldo<br />19 PAOLINI Luca<br />20 POZZATO Filippo<br />21 SANTAROMITA Ivan<br />22 SCARPONI Michele<br />23 ULISSI Diego<br />24 VANOTTI Alessandro<br />25 VISCONTI Giovanni</p> <p><strong>COLOMBIA</strong><br />26 ACEVEDO CALLE Janier<br />27 ANACONA GOMEZ Winner<br />28 ATAPUMA HURTADO Darwin<br />29 BETANCUR GOMEZ Carlos Alberto<br />30 HENAO MONTOYA Sergio Luis<br />31 QUINTANA ROJAS Nairo Alexander<br />32 RUBIANO CHAVEZ Miguel Angel<br />33 SARMIENTO TUNAROSA Jose Cayeta<br />34 URAN URAN Rigoberto</p> <p><strong>GREAT BRITAIN</strong><br />35 CAVENDISH Mark<br />36 CUMMINGS Stephen<br />37 EDMONDSON Joshua<br />38 FROOME Christopher<br />39 ROWE Luke<br />40 STANNARD Ian<br />41 THOMAS Geraint<br />42 WIGGINS Bradley</p> <p><strong>NETHERLANDS</strong><br />43 DUMOULIN Tom<br />44 GESINK Robert<br />45 HOOGERLAND Johnny<br />46 KELDERMAN Wilco<br />47 LANGEVELD Sebastian<br />48 MOLLEMA Bauke<br />49 SLAGTER Tom Jelte<br />50 TEN DAM Laurens<br />51 WEENING Pieter</p> <p><strong>FRANCE</strong><br />52 BARDET Romain<br />53 BARGUIL Warren<br />54 GAUTIER Cyril<br />55 MOINARD Amael<br />56 PINOT Thibaut<br />57 RIBLON Christophe<br />58 ROUX Anthony<br />59 VICHOT Arthur<br />60 VOECKLER Thomas</p> <p><strong>AUSTRALIA</strong><br />61 CLARKE Simon<br />62 DENNIS Rohan<br />63 EVANS Cadel<br />64 HAYMAN Mathew<br />65 MATTHEWS Michael<br />66 MEYER Cameron<br />67 PORTE Richie<br />68 SUTHERLAND Rory<br />69 TANNER David</p> <p><strong>UNITED STATES OF AMERICA</strong><br />70 BUSCHE Matthew<br />71 HORNER Christopher<br />72 HOWES Alex<br />73 PHINNEY Taylor<br />74 STETINA Peter<br />75 TALANSKY Andrew<br />76 VAN GARDEREN Tejay</p> <p><strong>SLOVAKIA</strong><br />77 JURCO Matej<br />78 SAGAN Juraj<br />79 SAGAN Peter<br />80 TYBOR Patrik<br />81 VELITS Martin<br />82 VELITS Peter</p> <p><strong>CZECH REPUBLIC</strong><br />83 BARTA Jan<br />84 HUNAL Martin<br />85 KOZUBEK Stanislav<br />86 NOVAK Jakub<br />87 RABON Frantisek<br />88 STYBAR Zdenek</p> <p><strong>SWITZERLAND</strong><br />89 ALBASINI Michael<br />90 CANCELLARA Fabian<br />91 ELMIGER Martin<br />92 FRANK Mathias<br />93 RAST Gregory<br />94 REICHENBACH Sebastien<br />95 SCHAR Michael<br />96 WYSS Danilo<br />97 ZAUGG Oliver</p> <p><strong>POLAND</strong><br />98 BODNAR Maciej<br />99 GOLAS Michal<br />100 HUZARSKI Bartosz<br />101 KWIATKOWSKI Michal<br />102 MAJKA Rafal<br />103 MARCZYNSKI Tomasz<br />104 NIEMIEC Przemyslaw<br />105 PATERSKI Maciej<br />106 SYLWESTER Szmyd</p> <p><strong>GERMANY</strong><br />107 BURGHARDT Marcus<br />108 DEGENKOLB John<br />109 GESCHKE Simon<br />110 MARTENS Paul<br />111 NERZ Dominik<br />112 WEGMANN Fabian</p> <p><strong>IRELAND</strong><br />113 BENNETT Sam<br />114 BRAMMEIER Matt<br />115 MARTIN Daniel<br />116 ROCHE Nicolas</p> <p><strong>UKRAINE</strong><br />117 BUTS Vitaliy<br />118 GRECHYN Sergiy<br />119 GRIVKO Andriy<br />120 KHRIPTA Andriy<br />121 KONONENKO Mykhaylo<br />122 POPOVYCH Yaroslav</p> <p><strong>SLOVENIA</strong><br />123 BOLE Grega<br />124 BOZIC Borut<br />125 BRAJKOVIC Janez<br />126 KOREN Kristijan<br />127 MATEJ Mugerli<br />128 POLANC Jan</p> <p><strong>AUSTRIA</strong><br />129 BRANDLE Matthias<br />130 DENIFL Stefan<br />131 EIBEGGER Markus<br />132 EISEL Bernhard<br />133 PREIDLER Georg<br />134 ZOIDL Riccardo</p> <p><strong>RUSSIAN FEDERATION</strong><br />135 CHERNETSKI Sergei<br />136 KOLO